==English==
===Etymology===
Old English [[berstan]], from Germanic ''*brestanan''.  Cognate with Dutch [[bersten]], [[barsten]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/bɜrst/}} ''(US)''
*{{IPA|/bɜ:st/}} ''(UK)''
*{{audio|en-us-burst.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Verb===
{{irregverb|'''to burst'''|'''bursts'''|'''burst'''|'''burst'''|'''[[bursting]]'''}}
# {{intransitive}} To break from internal pressure.
#: ''I blew the baloon up too much, and it '''burst'''.''
# {{transitive}} To cause to burst.
#: ''I '''burst''' the baloon when I blew it up too much.''

